- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with tilings, which are a discrete mathematical concept. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also likely as the paper characterizes the complexity classes of the sets of periods that a tiling system can produce. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper uses logical reasoning to prove its results. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with languages and their complexity. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is less likely but still possible as tilings can be seen as a form of geometric arrangement.
